09/10/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Lt Gen William Ward took command of the 17,000-strong SFOR on Tuesday (8 October) from Gen John Sylvester. 
In his first speech, Ward urged Bosnia and Herzegovina's newly elected leaders to work for the rule of law and for "sound economic reform". 
Gen Sylvester will become chief of staff of the US European Command.
In other news, a spokesman for the German peacekeepers announced Tuesday that the German and Italian brigades will come under joint command in mid-November as NATO streamlines its operations in Kosovo. 
The move will affect some 10,100 troops. 
(OHR Sources - 09/10/02; AP, AFP, RTRS - 08/10/02)
